production are pushing in the
other direction.

10:05.839 --> 10:07.907 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: How do you see
that, Scott
Paul?

10:07.941 --> 10:12.212 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Is this something that could be
replicated
company by company by company in
this country?

10:12.245 --> 10:13.980 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
SCOTT PAUL: Right.

10:14.013 --> 10:17.851 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Well, there's a company around
the corner
from Carrier, Rexnord, which
still plans to

10:17.884 --> 10:20.186 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
offshore production to Mexico.

10:20.220 --> 10:25.825 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And so from a case management
perspective,
there were about 1,600 plant
closures or notices

10:25.859 --> 10:28.828 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
over the last two years that are
related to
trade.

10:28.862 --> 10:31.564 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
It's impossible to work through
that list.

10:31.598 --> 10:36.870 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But I will also say that I think
an intervention
like this sends shockwaves
through corporate

10:36.903 --> 10:38.705 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
boardrooms.

10:38.738 --> 10:42.408 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
When they're making sourcing
decisions, they're
considering the labor cost
factor that Greg

10:42.442 --> 10:44.177 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
indicated.

10:44.210 --> 10:48.114 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
They also consider some the
risks that would
result from exiting the United
States and

10:48.147 --> 10:50.750 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
whether there could be other
consequences
for that as well.

10:50.783 --> 10:54.787 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And consequence,
excuse me,
is a term, Greg Ip, that the
president-elect

10:54.821 --> 10:56.689 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
used today.

10:56.723 --> 11:00.159 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
He said there will be
consequences when other
companies announce they are
leaving and moving

11:00.193 --> 11:01.728 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
jobs out of this country.

11:01.761 --> 11:03.663 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
What consequences could there
be?

11:03.696 --> 11:06.533 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GREG IP: Well, he hasn't been
specific, but
if you go back over some of the
campaign rhetoric,

11:06.566 --> 11:10.403 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
well, obviously, there's the
bully pulpit,
just publicly shaming these
companies.

11:10.436 --> 11:12.171 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And that again is not new to
Trump.

11:12.205 --> 11:17.143 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
If you remember, back in 2004,
John Kerry
was making noises about Benedict
Arnold CEOs

11:17.176 --> 11:18.878 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
in a similar context.

11:18.912 --> 11:22.615 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
So, that's got a long and
gloried tradition.

11:22.649 --> 11:27.320 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He can, for example, imply the
threat that
federal business will be
withheld from some

11:27.353 --> 11:28.788 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
of these companies.

11:28.821 --> 11:30.256 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
That's possibly dangerous
precedent.

11:30.290 --> 11:32.358 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
You know what I mean?

11:32.392 --> 11:36.429 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
When -- the Pentagon has very
specific guidelines,
for example, when it goes out
and does procurement.

11:36.462 --> 11:39.866 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
You don't want them buying a jet
engine which
is actually inferior to another
jet engine

11:39.899 --> 11:43.169 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
simply because that other
company outsourced
some jobs.

11:43.202 --> 11:48.775 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The final thing that Trump could
do is he
could impose tariffs on any
products that

11:48.808 --> 11:52.412 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
are imported once they have been
outsourced
to another country.

11:52.445 --> 11:54.213 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
It's not clear how they could do
it.

11:54.247 --> 11:56.282 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
The legal authority is somewhat
murky.

11:56.316 --> 11:58.885 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But there's not much question
that he could
do it if he wanted to do it.

11:58.918 --> 12:02.989 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And that's why people do worry
that we end
up with a trade war as a result
of these tactics.

12:03.022 --> 12:06.059 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Is that a concern
for the manufacturing
sector, Scott Paul?

12:06.092 --> 12:10.129 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
SCOTT PAUL: Well, I think a
full-blown trade
war is unlikely.

12:10.163 --> 12:14.968 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
There are a lot of safeguards in
place to
prevent it from escalating to
that point.

12:15.001 --> 12:19.539 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I think that there are a lot of
domestic businesses
that would argue we're in a
trade war with

12:19.572 --> 12:20.873 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
China now.

12:20.907 --> 12:23.710 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
We haven't pushed back all that
much.

12:23.743 --> 12:30.516 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And, again, the signal that this
sends to
corporate America and to our
trade partners

12:30.550 --> 12:32.251 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
is that we're going to drive a
tougher bargain.

12:32.285 --> 12:34.320 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I don't know that we have always
done that.

12:34.354 --> 12:39.459 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And depending on how it's
managed, it could
yield some returns for American
businesses

12:39.492 --> 12:40.827 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
and American workers.

12:40.860 --> 12:42.829 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And that's what
I'm trying
to understand, Greg Ip.

12:42.862 --> 12:50.003 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
On balance, is this move today
and maybe a
few other moves down the road
likely to alter

12:50.036 --> 12:55.642 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the health of the American
economy, the well-being
of American workers across the
board?

12:55.675 --> 13:00.446 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GREG IP: There's no question
that protectionist
or sort of moral suasion efforts
like this

13:00.480 --> 13:03.049 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
can make a difference on a
case-by-case basis.

13:03.082 --> 13:04.517 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
We have seen it in the past.

13:04.550 --> 13:09.088 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It will probably save a few
thousand, possibly
more, jobs this time.

13:09.122 --> 13:12.759 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But, as we were discussing
earlier, if the
economics are saying that this
is an expensive

13:12.792 --> 13:16.362 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
place to produce stuff, it's
very hard to
see that turning that around.

13:16.396 --> 13:20.500 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
That's why it would be more
useful to focus
on some of the other points that
I think Mr.

13:20.533 --> 13:24.237 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Trump was making today about
making this a
better place to manufacture.

13:24.270 --> 13:28.841 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And that's not really about like
threatening
or bribery, which is what
incentives really

13:28.875 --> 13:30.209 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
are.

13:30.243 --> 13:33.513 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It's about lower tax rates, less
regulation
and better education.

13:33.546 --> 13:39.185 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
There are 300,000 manufacturing
jobs that
are vacant right now because
employers are

13:39.218 --> 13:41.988 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
having trouble finding the right
skilled workers.

13:42.021 --> 13:47.293 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Back when the Carrier
announcement was made
earlier this year, the union
representative

13:47.326 --> 13:51.330 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
got a phone call from Boeing
saying, hey,
we need 60 skilled workers, are
your guys

13:51.364 --> 13:53.099 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
available?

13:53.132 --> 13:56.769 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Unfortunately, very few of those
people had
the skills necessary that Boeing
was looking

13:56.803 --> 13:57.770 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
for.

13:57.804 --> 13:58.771 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
JUDY WOODRUFF: That's
interesting.

13:58.805 --> 14:00.807 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
So, Scott Paul, again, same
question.

14:00.840 --> 14:07.447 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
On balance, is something like
this -- if Donald
Trump is talking about tax
reductions for

14:07.480 --> 14:11.350 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
corporations, talking about
doing away with
a lot of regulations, is that
going to create

14:11.384 --> 14:16.122 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
an environment where many
American companies
will decide not to send jobs
overseas?

14:16.155 --> 14:20.493 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SCOTT PAUL: Yes, I think Greg is
right that
the macro environment is going
to be critically

14:20.526 --> 14:22.295 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
important here.

14:22.328 --> 14:26.699 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And it's a combination of the
corporate tax
code, the strength of the
dollar, which is

14:26.733 --> 14:31.471 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
very important to our exporters,
the work
force, the investments that
we're making in

14:31.504 --> 14:36.943 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
our infrastructure, because
labor, quite honestly,
is becoming a smaller component
in the cost

14:36.976 --> 14:38.344 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
of manufacturing.

14:38.377 --> 14:40.546 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Energy, the materials make a big
difference.

14:40.580 --> 14:45.485 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And the other factor here is
that these countries
compete for business with us by
offering these

14:45.518 --> 14:47.220 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
subsidies all the time.

14:47.253 --> 14:50.690 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
If they see the United States is
in the game
of this, it could change the
equation.

14:50.723 --> 14:55.595 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Scott Paul, Greg
Ip, we thank
you both.

14:55.628 --> 15:00.233 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
GREG IP: Thank you.

15:00.266 --> 15:04.937 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
SCOTT PAUL: Thank you.

15:04.971 --> 15:10.543 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
HARI SREENIVASAN: The
six-week-long battle
for the ISIS-held city of Mosul
has become

15:10.576 --> 15:15.414 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
an increasingly tough urban war
for the American-backed
Iraqi forces.

15:15.448 --> 15:18.951 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Up to a million civilians still
live in the
city.

15:18.985 --> 15:23.356 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The front lines are often too
dangerous for
international aid workers, but
two young American

15:23.389 --> 15:27.794 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
volunteers are there saving
lives while risking
their own.

15:27.827 --> 15:32.398 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
From Mosul, special
correspondent Jane Ferguson
and producer Matt McGarry filed
this report.

15:32.431 --> 15:36.135 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
A warning: Viewers may find some
of the imagery
disturbing.

15:36.169 --> 15:43.676 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JANE FERGUSON: Crying in pain, a
tiny patient
is carried into this basic
treatment center

15:43.709 --> 15:45.678 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
in Mosul.

15:45.711 --> 15:48.848 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
His name is Karam.

15:48.881 --> 15:53.519 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And at just 5 years old, the
agony and fear
are too much.

15:53.553 --> 15:57.256 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
"Hawa" (ph), says his father,
mortar.

15:57.290 --> 16:00.459 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
His leg was shattered when it
was hit two
weeks ago.

16:00.493 --> 16:03.262 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
It was operated on, and is now
infected.

16:03.296 --> 16:06.866 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
His father tries to comfort him.

16:06.899 --> 16:15.041 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
For parents, war brings a
terrible fear of
loss.

16:15.074 --> 16:18.344 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Two American medics are helping
Karam.

16:18.377 --> 16:22.615 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
They have been at this post for
about a month,
treating civilians injured in
the fighting.

16:22.648 --> 16:24.317 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
How many of your patients are
children?

16:24.350 --> 16:25.318 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
PETE REED, Volunteer: Too many.

16:25.351 --> 16:27.253 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
DEREK COLEMAN, Volunteer: At
least a quarter.

16:27.286 --> 16:30.256 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JANE FERGUSON: Injured by?

16:30.289 --> 16:31.524 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
PETE REED: Everything.

16:31.557 --> 16:33.993 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
DEREK COLEMAN: Car bombs,
mortars, snipers.

16:34.026 --> 16:35.261 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
PETE REED: Shot.

16:35.294 --> 16:37.663 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JANE FERGUSON: Karam is lucky.

16:37.697 --> 16:41.100 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
He managed to find treatment
from ISIS doctors.

16:41.133 --> 16:45.338 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It's crude, but at least he will
be able to
walk again.

16:45.371 --> 16:48.207 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
He probably won't lose the leg.

16:48.241 --> 16:49.408 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Is this kind of injury common?

16:49.442 --> 16:51.277 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
PETE REED: The injury, yes.

16:51.310 --> 16:54.213 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And actually making it to
surgery was less
common?

16:54.247 --> 16:56.315 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JANE FERGUSON: So, where would
have gone for
the surgery?

16:56.349 --> 17:00.019 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
PETE REED: He went in Mosul.

17:00.052 --> 17:01.587 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
There are still operating
hospitals there.

17:01.621 --> 17:02.788 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JANE FERGUSON: Inside ISIS
territory?

17:02.822 --> 17:04.557 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
PETE REED: Yes.

17:04.590 --> 17:09.862 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
JANE FERGUSON: These two
American volunteers,
both just 27 years old, are the
first and

17:09.896 --> 17:15.201 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
only point of help civilians and
Iraqi army
soldiers get this close to the
front line

17:15.234 --> 17:19.805 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
of fighting in Mosul.

17:19.839 --> 17:22.775 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Pete Reed is from Bordentown,
New Jersey.

17:22.808 --> 17:28.281 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
After two tours in Afghanistan
as a Marine,
he came to Iraq to help.

17:28.314 --> 17:30.716 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Derek Coleman is from San Diego.

17:30.750 --> 17:36.022 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He was a machinist in a factory
with some
medical training before coming
here as a volunteer.

17:36.055 --> 17:38.925 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Â®MD-BO /DEREK COLEMAN: I don't
have any kids,
girlfriend, wife, nothing like
that.

17:38.958 --> 17:46.699 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So I wanted a little adventure,
and see ISIS
as an evil enemy, and saw good
people fighting

17:46.732 --> 17:49.035 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
against it, and I thought I
could help somehow.

17:49.068 --> 17:57.810 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And medical work seems to be
much more important
than carrying a gun and shooting
at people.

17:57.843 --> 18:03.082 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JANE FERGUSON: Other charities
are miles back
from the front lines, wary of
putting their

18:03.115 --> 18:04.884 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
staff in harm's way.

18:04.917 --> 18:11.190 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Because of ISIS suicide car
bombs, the civilians
of Mosul are banned from driving
cars.

18:11.223 --> 18:16.228 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Many of the injured wouldn't
survive if Pete
and Derek were not this close to
the fighting.

18:16.262 --> 18:20.066 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DEREK COLEMAN: The location is
everything
with what we are doing.

18:20.099 --> 18:23.569 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
NGOs and other organizations
can't get anywhere
close to where we are.

18:23.602 --> 18:29.008 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, what we are doing is, we are
stopping
bleeding that would kill someone
in five minutes.

18:29.041 --> 18:35.214 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We are stabilizing patients that
hopefully
survive the trip to the closest
hospital.

18:35.247 --> 18:39.885 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Even with us, the hospitals are
so far away
at this point, that we are
afraid of how many

18:39.919 --> 18:41.554 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
patients we lose on the road.

18:41.587 --> 18:47.259 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JANE FERGUSON: But being this
close to the
front puts Derek and Pete at
risk.

18:47.293 --> 18:51.964 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
They are always short on
supplies, so Pete
has gone out to search for any
other medical

18:51.998 --> 18:54.700 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
stations to ask for more.

18:54.734 --> 18:57.870 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Derek just begins telling us
about missing
the holiday.

18:57.903 --> 19:02.274 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DEREK COLEMAN: Thanksgiving was
interesting,
because Thanksgiving was also
when I left

19:02.308 --> 19:03.275 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
home last year.

19:03.309 --> 19:05.544 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
So, I had a turkey sandwich
alone.

19:05.578 --> 19:06.545 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(GUNFIRE)

19:06.579 --> 19:10.616 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
DEREK COLEMAN: That was a little
close.

19:10.649 --> 19:16.088 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JANE FERGUSON: Bullets start
flying, and we
have to run for cover.

19:16.122 --> 19:18.724 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
This is normal, this kind of
gunfire going
overhead?

19:18.758 --> 19:19.759 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
DEREK COLEMAN: Yes.

19:19.792 --> 19:21.193 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Yes, it's pretty normal.

19:21.227 --> 19:24.597 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Our proximity to the front line,
it's bound
to happen.

19:24.630 --> 19:27.867 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JANE FERGUSON: Derek calls to
warn Pete to
be careful.

19:27.900 --> 19:30.002 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
The fighting has intensified
around us.

19:30.036 --> 19:31.003 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
DEREK COLEMAN: Hey, buddy.

19:31.037 --> 19:32.805 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
How are you doing?

19:32.838 --> 19:37.710 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We have had quite a few rounds
pass really
close to our CCP here, worse
that yesterday.

19:37.743 --> 19:40.613 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So I just wanted to give you
guys a warning
as you are pulling up and just
check in with

19:40.646 --> 19:42.515 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
you.

19:42.548 --> 19:47.019 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JANE FERGUSON: In the meantime,
Derek prepares
for the next patients, which
will surely come.

19:47.053 --> 19:50.823 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The conditions here are harsh,
but they have
learned to manage.

19:50.856 --> 19:55.628 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DEREK COLEMAN: As you can see,
I'm kind of
bloodied here, and I don't
really have time

19:55.661 --> 19:57.263 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
to always clean it all off.

19:57.296 --> 20:02.601 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So I just try to not look like a
I came out
of a butcher shop as best I can.

20:02.635 --> 20:10.643 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JANE FERGUSON: Pete arrives back
empty-handed,
his search for supplies
unsuccessful, just

20:10.676 --> 20:13.746 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
as more patients are brought in.

20:13.779 --> 20:19.919 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The center is also the first
point of treatment
for many Iraqi soldiers, their
bodies brutalized

20:19.952 --> 20:25.825 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
by the urban warfare that rages
just down
the road.

20:25.858 --> 20:34.567 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We are not allowed to film the
injured and
dying soldiers who arrived at
the center.

20:34.600 --> 20:39.872 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Iraqi special forces medics are
here too,
some trained by the two young
Americans.

20:39.905 --> 20:46.645 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
They often treat civilians, many
transported
here by the army in
war-weathered Humvees.

20:46.679 --> 20:52.585 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Soon, one pulls up, and a child
wrapped in
a blanket is lifted from it.

20:52.618 --> 20:55.855 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
A soldier races her into the
center.

20:55.888 --> 21:03.462 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
Her aunt stays outside,
hysterical with fear
and grief.

21:03.496 --> 21:08.734 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
MAN: Hold her (EXPLETIVE
DELETED) head, somebody.

21:08.767 --> 21:13.906 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JANE FERGUSON: The small girl
has been shot
in the head by an ISIS sniper.

21:13.939 --> 21:19.445 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Incredibly, she is still alive.

21:19.478 --> 21:22.214 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Pete and Derek fight hard to
save her life.

21:22.248 --> 21:25.584 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
PETE REED: Tell her to stay
still, stay still.

21:25.618 --> 21:29.221 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JANE FERGUSON: They manage to
bandage her
head.

21:29.255 --> 21:34.860 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
PETE REED: Plaster, plaster.

21:34.894 --> 21:44.403 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JANE FERGUSON: Despite brave
efforts, the
little girl died.

21:44.436 --> 21:50.342 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Do you think, given what you
have witnessed,
that ISIS are deliberating
targeting civilians?

21:50.376 --> 21:52.444 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
PETE REED: Yes.

21:52.478 --> 21:54.914 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
They are shooting people with
white flags.

21:54.947 --> 21:58.050 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
They are shooting kids.

21:58.083 --> 22:02.154 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Last week, we had two kids in a
row who had
been shot in the neck or the
head by a Da'esh

22:02.188 --> 22:09.094 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
sniper because they were fleeing
Mosul, not
accidental grazing fire or
anything like that,

22:09.128 --> 22:15.801 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
proper sniper shots, head and
neck and face.

22:15.834 --> 22:20.673 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Yes, they're -- they're
purposely trying to
kill these people who are
running away.

22:20.706 --> 22:25.878 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JANE FERGUSON: Being in the
crossfire and
tending to death, his family are
worried about

22:25.911 --> 22:27.146 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
him.

22:27.179 --> 22:33.319 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
PETE REED: Yes, they worry a
lot, probably
for good reason.

22:33.352 --> 22:34.587 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Who wouldn't worry?

22:34.620 --> 22:38.490 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It's not like, I don't know, a
ski instructor
in Wyoming.

22:38.524 --> 22:41.393 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I'm on the front lines in the
battle for Mosul.

22:41.427 --> 22:43.028 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
They are really, really
supportive.

22:43.062 --> 22:45.197 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
They're just terrified of what
I'm doing.

22:45.231 --> 22:46.198 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JANE FERGUSON: Are you changed?

22:46.232 --> 22:47.433 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
PETE REED: Am I changed?

22:47.466 --> 22:49.268 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
Yes.

22:49.301 --> 22:55.140 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
You can only see so many dead
kids a day so
many days in a row before you
are going to

22:55.174 --> 22:56.976 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
be changed.

22:57.009 --> 23:00.512 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
People see one dead kid or one
traumatic thing
happen, and it affects them for
the rest of

23:00.546 --> 23:01.614 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
their life.

23:01.647 --> 23:04.883 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
I have seen a couple hundred.

23:04.917 --> 23:08.087 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
I'm doing OK.

23:08.120 --> 23:16.161 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JANE FERGUSON: Inside, spirits
are high, because
Karam, the first child we met,
is feeling

23:16.195 --> 23:17.429 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
better.

23:17.463 --> 23:20.399 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
A little tenderness and some
candy have helped.

23:20.432 --> 23:24.737 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He has been fortunate to cheat
death in this
violent place.

23:24.770 --> 23:37.283 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
For the "PBS NewsHour," I'm Jane
Ferguson
in Mosul, Iraq.

23:37.316 --> 23:46.725 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Stay with us.

23:46.759 --> 23:52.197 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Coming up on the "NewsHour": the
link between
distrust of government and
crumbling infrastructure;

23:52.231 --> 23:57.836 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and an author's take on changing
how society
thinks about marijuana.

23:57.870 --> 24:00.639 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
But first: Today is World AIDS
Day.

24:00.673 --> 24:05.311 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
While the death toll from AIDS
has dropped
dramatically, the virus still
claims over

24:05.344 --> 24:10.282 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
a million people every year, and
nearly 40
million remain infected.

24:10.316 --> 24:12.017 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
William Brangham has an update.

24:12.051 --> 24:15.954 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: With the
growing use of
medications to treat and prevent
the spread

24:15.988 --> 24:20.959 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
of HIV, some say ending the AIDS
epidemic
is actually within reach.

24:20.993 --> 24:25.464 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But AIDS is still the number one
killer of
reproductive age women, and in
many places,

24:25.497 --> 24:28.334 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
those lifesaving drugs are
barely available.

24:28.367 --> 24:29.735 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Scientists are also seeking a
vaccine.

24:29.768 --> 24:32.871 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
A new trial is under way right
now in South
Africa.

24:32.905 --> 24:34.740 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
But many remain skeptical.

24:34.773 --> 24:39.178 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I'm joined now by "Science"
magazine's Jon
Cohen, who's covered this
epidemic for nearly

24:39.211 --> 24:43.816 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
30 years and was a collaborator
with us on
our recent series about HIV and
AIDS.

24:43.849 --> 24:46.685 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Jon Cohen, welcome back to the
"NewsHour."

24:46.719 --> 24:49.888 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Let's start off by talking about
this vaccine
trial in South Africa.

24:49.922 --> 24:54.793 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
As you well know, you wrote the
book about
the hunt for an HIV vaccine.

24:54.827 --> 24:56.395 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
What is happening in South
Africa right now?

24:56.428 --> 24:58.297 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Is this as promising as some
think it is?

24:58.330 --> 25:02.301 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JON COHEN, "Science": Well, the
AIDS vaccine
is the Holy Grail.

25:02.334 --> 25:05.137 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
People can come in, get a few
shots, be protected
for life.

25:05.170 --> 25:06.972 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
That's the dream.

25:07.005 --> 25:12.644 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In Thailand in 2009, it was
revealed that
a vaccine being studied there
protected people

25:12.678 --> 25:16.281 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
with about a 31 percent
reduction in risk.

25:16.315 --> 25:17.349 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
That's not very good.

25:17.383 --> 25:19.284 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
That's extremely low, but it was
something.

25:19.318 --> 25:21.153 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
It was the first glimmer of
hope.

25:21.186 --> 25:25.023 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The vaccine trial in South
Africa is building
off that Thai trial.

25:25.057 --> 25:28.060 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The results from the Thai trial
were extremely
controversial.

25:28.093 --> 25:32.931 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
There are people who wonder why
that vaccine
strategy has moved forward in
South Africa,

25:32.965 --> 25:37.836 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and there are South Africans who
argue very
strongly that this is a great
hope for them,

25:37.870 --> 25:41.940 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and even if they get some
protection, in addition
to other protective measures, it
could make

25:41.974 --> 25:42.941 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
a big difference.

25:42.975 --> 25:43.909 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: OK.

25:43.942 --> 25:45.477 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Now let's talk a little bit more
broadly

25:45.511 --> 25:48.547 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
Where are the successes
currently in the fight
against HIV?

25:48.580 --> 25:50.582 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
And where are those happening?

25:50.616 --> 25:55.053 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JON COHEN: Well, clearly,
preventing mother-to-child
transmission has been a huge
success all around

25:55.087 --> 25:56.355 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
the world.

25:56.388 --> 25:59.725 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It's one of the easiest things
to do in terms
of prevention.

25:59.758 --> 26:04.296 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And some countries like South
Africa have
reduced it to below 2 percent of
pregnant

26:04.329 --> 26:06.932 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
women who are infected passing
on the virus.

26:06.965 --> 26:08.700 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
That's a great success.

26:08.734 --> 26:12.671 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Treatment now has scaled up from
basically
being zero in poor countries
around the world

26:12.704 --> 26:20.045 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
in the year 2000 to 18.2 million
of the 36.7
million infected people.

26:20.078 --> 26:21.947 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Phenomenal success story.

26:21.980 --> 26:26.351 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
People who are treated and stay
on treatment
fully suppress the virus and
they rarely transmit

26:26.385 --> 26:27.719 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
to others.

26:27.753 --> 26:30.689 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So that is leading to hope that
epidemics
can stop petering out.

26:30.722 --> 26:33.225 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: What about the
remaining
challenges?

26:33.258 --> 26:37.996 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Obviously, there are still
troubling high
rates of HIV among particular
populations

26:38.030 --> 26:39.398 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
around the world.

26:39.431 --> 26:42.000 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
You and I saw that as we
traveled through
Africa and here in the U.S.

26:42.034 --> 26:44.036 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
What are the other big
challenges facing AIDS?

26:44.069 --> 26:49.074 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JON COHEN: So, one big challenge
is that only
half the people who need
treatment are getting

26:49.107 --> 26:50.075 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
treatment.

26:50.108 --> 26:51.944 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
So, that's an enormous
challenge.

26:51.977 --> 26:53.579 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And the other one, as you
mentioned, is there
are a lot of young people who
are getting

26:53.612 --> 26:54.980 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
infected.

26:55.013 --> 26:58.150 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I mean, 2.1 million people are
still getting
infected every year.

26:58.183 --> 27:00.486 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And that number isn't changing
very much.

27:00.519 --> 27:06.525 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So something needs to be done
particularly
to reach young women in much of
sub-Saharan

27:06.558 --> 27:08.360 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Africa, who are highly
vulnerable.

27:08.393 --> 27:13.932 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And it is really unclear in many
places, like
South Africa, why they're
becoming infected

27:13.966 --> 27:15.701 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
at such extraordinarily high
rates.

27:15.734 --> 27:19.938 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: UNICEF
recently put out
a very stark warning, saying
that if prevention

27:19.972 --> 27:25.310 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
efforts weren't ramped up, we
would see what
they argued was a real spike in
new incidences

27:25.344 --> 27:28.380 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
amongst adolescents.

27:28.413 --> 27:29.681 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
What can be done to do that?

27:29.715 --> 27:32.384 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Are you hopeful that we can
actually nip that
in the bud?

27:32.417 --> 27:35.554 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JON COHEN: It's one of the most
vexing problems.

27:35.587 --> 27:37.222 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
I mean, there are a few
problems.

27:37.256 --> 27:39.358 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
One is adolescents are
risk-takers.

27:39.391 --> 27:42.294 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Any of us who have adolescents
certainly know
that.

27:42.327 --> 27:46.431 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
And they don't perceive
themselves as being
in harm's way, even when it's
clear that there

27:46.465 --> 27:48.534 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
is a lot of HIV in their
community.

27:48.567 --> 27:52.371 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The other is, some adolescents
are infected
at birth, and they are only
learning about

27:52.404 --> 27:57.209 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
their infection, as you and I
saw in Rwanda,
when they get to be teenagers
and get sick.

27:57.242 --> 28:00.812 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And then they have trouble
staying on medication
because there is a lot of
resentment about

28:00.846 --> 28:04.750 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the fact that they were infected
and nobody
told them the truth about, let's
say, how

28:04.783 --> 28:06.218 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
their mother died.

28:06.251 --> 28:10.722 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
So, both of those things
combined create a
really, really big problem.

28:10.756 --> 28:12.090 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
And there's no easy solution.

28:12.124 --> 28:14.893 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: Lastly, Jon,
what about
the issue of funding?

28:14.927 --> 28:19.932 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
As we traveled across much of
South Africa,
we heard repeatedly that funding
is an issue.

28:19.965 --> 28:22.000 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
What is the trend line looking
in that regard?

28:22.034 --> 28:26.572 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JON COHEN: The world is short
about $7 billion
a year, according to UNAIDS'
estimates.

28:26.605 --> 28:28.740 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And so the question is, where is
more money
going to come from?

28:28.774 --> 28:32.544 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Is it going to come donor
wealthy countries
or domestic sources?

28:32.578 --> 28:34.313 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Both are strapped.

28:34.346 --> 28:38.050 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
There's hope that, with evidence
of things
working in countries like Malawi
and Zimbabwe

28:38.083 --> 28:43.889 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and Zambia, which today report
that they have
had phenomenal success keeping
people suppressed

28:43.922 --> 28:48.427 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and on treatment, that that will
lead funders
to think this investment is
worth it and let's

28:48.460 --> 28:50.429 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
put some more into control this
thing once
and for all.

28:50.462 --> 28:51.530 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: All right.

28:51.563 --> 28:53.999 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
"Science" magazine's Jon Cohen,
thank you
so much.

28:54.032 --> 28:57.970 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
You can find additional
reporting on AIDS
from our series that aired last
summer.

28:58.003 --> 29:05.978 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
That's on our Web site,
PBS.org/NewsHour.

29:06.011 --> 29:18.190 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
HARI SREENIVASAN: Now
infrastructure investment
may be moving back front and
center.

29:18.223 --> 29:21.193 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
President-elect Trump plans to
push for it
through the private sector.

29:21.226 --> 29:24.696 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Democrats in Congress remain
interested in
greater public investment.

29:24.730 --> 29:28.700 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Our economics correspondent,
Paul Solman,
